    "narrative": "Today\u2019s optimal lineup for the Austin Waves is anchored by **Luis Robert Jr.**, who carries our highest efficiency score of 73.74. He benefits significantly from a 14% platoon boost against the southpaw Rodriguez, making him our primary offensive engine for this slate. Following closely are **Jacob Wilson** (64.54) and **Jorge Polanco** (63.80). **Jacob Wilson** remains a staple at the top of the order; his lead-off spot provides an automatic 10% projection bump, and he maintains a clean matchup against Weathers. **Jorge Polanco** also finds a favorable environment, as his 12% SP skill advantage against the mid-tier Rodriguez offsets a slight park penalty, solidifying his role in the middle of our production. **Miguel Vargas** and **Jackson Merrill** round out the active starters, both holding steady at scores of 60.08 and 57.92, respectively, maintaining the high floor we demand for daily games cap preservation.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision was the exclusion of **Liam Hicks**, who sits on the bench with a 38.51 score. While he enjoyed a double-digit platoon advantage against the right-handed Lowder, the elite 1.64 xERA of the opposing starter created a 19% handicap that dragged his efficiency well below our 40.0 \"Zebras Floor.\" Conversely, we are navigating a light schedule with **Gunnar Henderson**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Andy Pages** all inactive due to team off-days, which limits our ceiling and puts extra pressure on the starters to convert R and RBI opportunities. We are monitoring the official batting orders for **Miguel Vargas**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Jackson Merrill** closely; any downward movement in the lineup order for these players would necessitate a re-evaluation of their projected utility.",
